# Angular Feature Architecture

- Keep feature code under `src/app/features/<entity>/` with `models`, `data`, `state`, and `ui` folders.
- Treat page components as orchestration containers: store/repository calls, reactive form ownership, and toast decisions stay in page files.
- Move presentational and reusable view pieces into components, not into repositories or stores.
- Prefer incremental extraction: shared presentational primitives first, then feature-local components, then broader reuse.
- Keep existing route entry points stable while refactoring internals.
- Maintain existing behavior during refactors (delete/archive semantics, sheet actions, and combobox flows).
